{
  "stem": "4272.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mm-hm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- well, the one that they sent me to was this-- Bodzentyn, which was a small little town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My parents were sent to Starachowice, which was not far from that town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- but later when I found out where they were, I went there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was the town, actually, where they had the labor camp, that I was taken into that labor camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was in Starachowice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it's-- it's real hard for me to-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] let's see, '41, '42.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, well, we went through-- I went through a winter there, I'm sure.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that must have been like the next spring-- in the summertime, I was taken to the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my [INAUDIBLE]-- my parents were taken away a day before, and I didn't know where they were taking them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we didn't know what's going to happen to my sister and myself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then, the next morning, about 5:00 in the morning, 6:00 in the morning, we heard Juden raus, Juden raus, so we all had to go, like, to the marketplace.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's when we saw already what went on-- the-- the Gestapo, and-- and they were-- they were selecting people who was on the train right away that-- which needs to be killed.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the younger people, they left to take to camp to work for them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were-- there were-- there were terrible, terrible scenes at the time because they made mothers leave their children and go-- go to work, and the-- the-- the children were plain just thrown in on the train, lay there And whoever had a-- a bandage on, or-- or I had a friend that had a-- a broken leg and he was walking on with a crutch, and they killed him immediately.",
      "word_count": 72
    }
  ],
